byline.contributor: Jonathan Martin reported from Washington, and Michael Wines from New York.
byline.original: By JONATHAN MARTIN and MICHAEL WINES

abstract: News Analysis; Pres-elect Donald Trump easily clears 270-vote threshold in Electoral College to secure presidency, but protests at state capitols where electors cast their votes suggests country's divisions remain raw as Trump prepares to take office; liberals appear to be committed to confronting Trump, even as he scorns his critics.
lead_paragraph: Electors across the country faced protests, reflecting a vast divide that carried over from a tumultuous race and that the new president will be facing.

headline.main: Electoral College Settles Donald Trump’s Victory, but Little Else
headline.print_headline: Trump’s Win, but Little Else, Is Now Settled
